The Role of Technology in International Business: Digital Transformation and Global Operations (the-role-of-technology-in-international-business-digital-transformation-and-glob)

Date: [Insert Date]   |   Class time: 90 minutes   |   Course: International_Business   |   Lesson #31

Subject of Lesson

The Impact of Digital Transformation on International Business Operations

Required Materials

Case study on digital transformation in a global company (e.g., Amazon, Alibaba, or Maersk). Video clip on the impact of AI and blockchain on international business. Whiteboard or flip chart for group brainstorming and discussions. Online access to tools like cloud platforms, or live demonstration of AI capabilities, if possible.

Hook / Introduction

Start with a question: How do you think digital technologies like AI, blockchain, and the IoT are changing how global businesses operate? Can you think of any real-world examples where technology has given a company a competitive advantage? Show a short video on digital transformation in business, focusing on how companies like Amazon or Alibaba use technology to enhance global operations and efficiency.

Lesson Activities

1. Case Study Digital Transformation at Amazon

Type: Case Study   Duration: 30 minutes

Overview of Amazon's digital transformation strategies, group activity to analyze AI, cloud computing, blockchain, and IoT in Amazon's operations, and group presentations.

2. Class Discussion The Future of Digital Transformation in International Business

Type: Discussion   Duration: 20 minutes

Discuss how digital transformation helps companies compete in emerging markets, potential risks, and ethical considerations of using AI, IoT, and blockchain in global business.

3. Mini-Lecture Introduction to Digital Transformation in Global Business

Type: Lecture   Duration: 20 minutes

Discuss the definition of digital transformation, technologies driving transformation (AI, blockchain, cloud computing, IoT), and the benefits and challenges of digital transformation in global business.

Learning Objectives

  • Understand the impact of digital technologies on global business operations.
  • Analyze how international companies use AI, blockchain, and other digital tools to enhance efficiency and market access.
  • Evaluate the challenges and opportunities posed by digital transformation in international business.

Content Standards

  • AACSB Standard 9 Curriculum Content: Emphasize the role of digital technologies in optimizing global business strategies.
  • Learning Outcome 6: Analyze Global Financial Markets: Understand how technology facilitates international business operations and decision-making in global markets.

PRME Characteristics

  • Iterative Allow students to revisit their understanding of digital tools through case studies and practical application in discussions.
  • Actively Engaging Use interactive tools and discussions to explore how technology can address key challenges in global operations.
  • Socially Interactive Facilitate group discussions around the implications of digital transformation and collaborative technologies.
  • Meaningful Connect the latest technological advancements to real-world business examples in international markets.
  • Joyful Inspire curiosity and excitement about the potential of new technologies in transforming international business.

Sustainable Development Goals

  • SDG 9 Industry, Innovation, and Infrastructure Promote innovation through the use of advanced technologies in business practices.

Activity-specific Resources

  • Digital Transformation Simulation Worksheet (Worksheet) - Students will analyze a global company's use of digital technologies and assess the benefits, challenges, and strategies for digital transformation.

Rubrics

  • Digital Transformation Evaluation Rubric
    • Identification of Technologies (15 points)
    • Benefits and Challenges Assessment (15 points)
    • Technology Implementation Strategy (10 points)
    • Future Outlook (10 points)

Additional Files

  • Lesson 31/The-Role-of-Technology-in-International-Business.pptx

Assessment

Summative Assessment: Students will be assessed on their participation in the group activity, the depth of their analysis of Amazons digital transformation, and the quality of their contributions during the class discussion.

Data Analysis & Reflections

Evaluate group presentations and class discussions to ensure students understood the role of digital transformation in international business and could apply their insights to real-world business scenarios.

Did students engage effectively with the case study and discussion on digital transformation? Were they able to analyze the technologies impact on global business operations?

Differentiations

For Advanced Students: Assign a more complex case study involving multiple technologies and markets (e.g., exploring Alibabas digital ecosystem and how it operates globally). For Struggling Students: Provide additional guidance on understanding the technologies discussed, and break down how they directly impact business operations in simpler terms.

Extensions

Homework: Research how another global company (e.g., Tesla, Uber, or Maersk) has implemented digital transformation in its operations, and write a report on the challenges and successes of their approach.
